---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="ToolCraft privacy policy — we take your privacy seriously."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
        <span>Privacy Policy</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-content">
      <h2>Our Commitment to Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        ToolCraft is built with privacy as a core principle. We minimize data collection 
        and never sell or share your personal information.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect minimal information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Basic analytics</strong> — Anonymous page view counts to understand which tools are popular.</li>
        <li><strong>Contact form data</strong> — If you reach out, we keep your name and email to respond.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What We DON'T Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We <strong>do not</strong> upload or store files you process through our tools.</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not</strong> use cookies for tracking or advertising.</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not</strong> require accounts or email sign-ups to use tools.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Local Processing</h2>
      <p>
        All PDF, image, and document processing happens entirely in your browser. 
        Your files never leave your device. This means your documents, images, and data 
        remain private and under your control.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We may use minimal third-party services (e.g., hosting, CDN) that have their own 
        privacy policies. These are limited to infrastructure only — no analytics trackers, 
        no ad networks, no social media pixels.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related questions, <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <p><em>Last updated: December 2025</em></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
